The paper focuses on developing a novel deep convolutional neural network for hyperspectral image classification, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of image data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and optimization methods, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of spectral and spatial information, which is relevant to sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
